subsection.p:
We have already started building our list of derivatives of simple functions. We have shown, in Examples,, and, that
\diff{}{x} 1 &= 0 & \diff{}{x} x &= 1 & \diff{}{x} x^2 &= 2x & \diff{}{x} \sqrt{x} &= \frac{1}{2\sqrt{x}}
We'll expand this list later.

statement.p:
Let g(x) be a differentiable function. Then the derivative of the reciprocal of g is  given by


  \diff{}{x} \left\{ \frac{1}{g(x)} \right\} &= -\frac{g'(x)}{g(x)^2}


and exists except at those points where g(x)=0.
